column3: A fixed base that serves as the stationary mounting point for the ring. It appears to be solid and sturdy, likely designed to be attached to a surface.
A circular ring connected to the fixed base. It is designed to revolve around its attachment point, suggesting functionality for hanging or holding items.
A fixed base frame that serves as the foundation for the cabinet and supports the doors.
A revolute door on the left side of the cabinet that can swing open.
A revolute door on the right side of the cabinet that can swing open.
A fixed handle on the left door, designed to provide grip for opening the door.
A fixed handle on the left door, located symmetrically near the other handle, providing additional grip.
A fixed handle on the right door, designed to provide grip for opening the door.
A fixed handle on the right door, located symmetrically near the other handle, providing additional grip.
